        {
          "content": "{\n  \"buggy_files\": [\"drivers/ata/libata-core.c\"],\n  \"buggy_functions\": [\"ata_device_blacklist\"],\n  \"confidence\": 0.95,\n  \"reasoning\": \"The Samsung 860 EVO SSD is not present in the ata_device_blacklist table (around line 4393-4618). While Samsung SSD 840 and 850 models are listed with ATA_HORKAGE_NO_NCQ_TRIM flag to disable queued TRIM operations, the 860 EVO model is missing. This causes the device to attempt NCQ TRIM commands, which it doesn't properly handle, resulting in FPDMA QUEUED command timeouts and 20-30 second lockups during fstrim. The fix requires adding an entry: { \\\"Samsung SSD 860*\\\", NULL, ATA_HORKAGE_NO_NCQ_TRIM | ATA_HORKAGE_ZERO_AFTER_TRIM } to the blacklist table after line 4565. The ATA_HORKAGE_NO_NCQ_TRIM flag is checked in the ata_dev_config_ncq_send_recv() function (line 2218) to disable queued TRIM support for affected devices.\"\n}\n",
